---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---
<DocsLayout
	slug="workflows/dependabot-ci-fix"
	description="The Dependabot CI fix workflow — react to a dependency-update PR whose checks failed, push a fix, and auto-merge trivial ones."
>
	<p>
		Dependabot CI fix reacts when a dependency-update PR (Dependabot or Renovate)
		goes red in CI. When a check suite completes with a failure, Last Light
		diagnoses the breakage, pushes the smallest fix that makes CI pass, and —
		only when the change is trivial — enables GitHub auto-merge so the update
		lands once the re-run checks are green.
	</p>

	<div class="docs-callout tip">
		<div class="docs-callout-body">
			<strong>Permission profile:</strong> <code>repo-write</code> — can push
			commits to the PR branch and enable auto-merge. It never merges a red PR:
			auto-merge is gated on the required checks passing.
		</div>
	</div>

	<h2>Pipeline</h2>

	<div class="workflow-diagram">
		<svg viewBox="0 0 320 80" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
			<rect x="12" y="12" width="130" height="56" rx="8" fill="var(--bg-card)" stroke="var(--diag-line)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
			<text x="77" y="37" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--text)" font-size="11" font-family="Inter">Fix</text>
			<text x="77" y="52" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--diag-grey)" font-size="8" font-family="JetBrains Mono">diagnose + push</text>
			<path d="M146 40 H172" stroke="var(--diag-line)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
			<path d="M168 36 L174 40 L168 44 Z" fill="var(--diag-line)"/>
			<rect x="178" y="12" width="130" height="56" rx="8" fill="var(--bg-card)" stroke="var(--diag-line)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
			<text x="243" y="37" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--text)" font-size="11" font-family="Inter">Assess</text>
			<text x="243" y="52" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--diag-grey)" font-size="8" font-family="JetBrains Mono">trivial? → auto-merge</text>
		</svg>
	</div>

	<h2>What it does</h2>

	<ul>
		<li>Clones the repo at the PR's head branch (the dependency bump is already committed there)</li>
		<li>Reads the CI failures and diagnoses the cause — a stale lockfile, a breaking change in the new version, a call site or type that needs updating</li>
		<li>Makes the smallest fix that turns CI green, runs the test / lint / typecheck gate, and pushes to the PR branch</li>
		<li>Assesses the resulting diff: only lockfile / type-only / non-functional changes count as <strong>trivial</strong></li>
		<li>If trivial, enables GitHub auto-merge (squash) so the PR merges once checks pass; otherwise it comments and leaves the PR for a human</li>
	</ul>

	<div class="docs-callout note">
		<div class="docs-callout-body">
			Auto-merge needs "Allow auto-merge" enabled on the repository and at least
			one required status check. If it isn't available, the workflow comments
			that the fix looks trivial and asks a maintainer to merge.
		</div>
	</div>

	<h2>Triggers</h2>

	<ul>
		<li><strong>GitHub webhook:</strong> a <code>check_suite.completed</code> event with a <code>failure</code> / <code>timed_out</code> conclusion (surfaced internally as <code>pr.checks_failed</code>). The router runs it through the intent classifier, which routes a recognised dependency-update PR here. Requires the GitHub App to subscribe to <strong>Check suite</strong> events (Checks: read).</li>
	</ul>

	<p>
		Because routing goes through the classifier rather than a fixed rule, other
		workflows can react to the same failing-checks event by declaring their own
		<code>classification</code> block — this workflow simply claims the
		dependency-update case.
	</p>

	<div class="docs-next">
		<a href="/docs/workflows/pr-fix" class="prev">
			<span class="label">&larr; Prev</span>
			<span class="title">PR fix</span>
		</a>
		<a href="/docs/workflows/repo-health" class="next">
			<span class="label">Next &rarr;</span>
			<span class="title">Repo health</span>
		</a>
	</div>
</DocsLayout>

<style is:global>
	.workflow-diagram {
		margin: 1.5rem 0;
		padding: 1.25rem;
		background: var(--bg-card);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 10px;
		overflow-x: auto;
	}

	.workflow-diagram svg {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 320px;
		height: auto;
		display: block;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}
</style>
